title: cityism Volume I
author: citylion
pages:
#- -------------------§5cityism Volume I§0
§0-------------------  In times past, the citizens of a city state realized the truth, rose up, and awakened the great city from a thousand year slumber. The citizens understood a new way, and wrote down their new
#- principles, the principles of the great city.§0
§0 The great city can not be entirely described through words in the physical plane. It is not a place in most contexts. 
#- The first core tenet§0
§0------------------- The first core tenet of cityism states that cityists should spread and explain cityism to others. This is essential to the preservation of the cause. Cityism is a way of thinking that is new to the public, it
#- therefore must be discussed so those who would like to support causes similar to the cityist one, can be made aware that such a movement exists.
#- The second core tenet§0
§0------------------- The second core tenet of cityism is to include city when referring to a cityist. cityists usually include city in their name in cityist forums. 
#- The third core tenet§0
§0------------------- The third tenet of cityism states that those who oppose the cityist cause should not be hated upon. 
#- The forth core tenet§0
§0------------------- The forth core tenet of cityism states that cityists should help build bunkers for their cities, in efforts to protect the general public e.g. from raiders. Cities must be able to independently defend themselves if
#- necessary. Training sessions should be supplemeted to strengthen the city, and prepare the citizens.
#- The fifth core tenet§0
§0------------------- The fifth core tenet of cityism is to not fight the oppressors and censors of the cityist cause with aggression, as they perform evil, but instead to fight them with the word of the city.
#- The sixth core tenet§0
§0------------------- The sixth core tenet of cityism advocates for the creation of public experience production in cities, to make the city a living and breathing hub for production. 
#- The seventh tenet§0
§0------------------- The seventh tenet of cityism states that citizens under ineffective governments should be united. Then, they should work towards a more effective and free government. 
#- The eigth core tenet§0
§0------------------- The eight core tenet of cityism is to promote beneficial knowledge and discourse. Therefore, cityists should avoid censoring knowledge in cityist forums. 
#- The ninth core tenet§0
§0------------------- The ninth core tenet of cityism states that cityists should stay united with the city, and preserve the cause. Which is to say, cityists should not take extremeist stances, nor should they assult the cause. 
#- ------------------- Cityism can not exactly be described as a religion, nor as a following, but more as a way of thought. §0
§0 Many cityists have been observed as including a [TCS] before their name to display approval for the cause.
#- 